[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 36    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L141** ŌĆö TODO (TechWriter): Networking review N2 / Architecture A9 (LOW). Configure the standardization-vendor egress and the NCOA-vendor egress as distinct outbound proxy rules with non-overlapping allow-lists scoped to compute roles: the standardization Lambda's role allows only the CASS-certified-vendor API domain; the NCOA-result-handler Lambda's role allows only the NCOA-vendor secure-file-exchange domain. Per-role rate limit on vendor API calls below the vendor's published rate limits. Egress connections CloudWatch-logged for chargeback and forensic auditing. At volumes exceeding ~1M vendor API calls/month, evaluate the vendor's PrivateLink endpoint where available (eliminates NAT Gateway data-transfer cost on the egress path and keeps traffic on the AWS network).
